---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getStaticPagePathRecord } from '../../lib/static-page-slugs';
---
<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy Policy – kittokit"
  description="Privacy policy of kittokit: what data we process, on what legal basis, and how you can exercise your rights under the GDPR."
  pathWithoutLang={getStaticPagePathRecord('privacy')}
>
  <article class="legal">

    <header class="legal-header">
      <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: April 2026 · <a href="/en/imprint" class="legal-link">Imprint</a></p>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-body">

      <!-- Summary -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <div class="legal-infobox">
          <p class="infobox-lead">The short version</p>
          <ul class="infobox-list">
            <li>All tool calculations and conversions run <strong>entirely in your browser</strong> — no file uploads, no server-side processing.</li>
            <li>We use <strong>no tracking cookies</strong> and no cross-site tracking.</li>
            <li>Cloudflare Web Analytics is privacy-first, cookie-free, and creates no user profiles.</li>
            <li>Microsoft Clarity and Google AdSense are activated <strong>only after your explicit consent</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 1. Controller -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Controller</h2>
        <p>The controller for data processing on this website is the private individual operating kittokit as a non-commercial hobby project.</p>
        <dl class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Project</dt>
            <dd>kittokit — non-commercial hobby project, no advertising revenue</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Location</dt>
            <dd>Germany</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Contact</dt>
            <dd><a href="mailto:hello@kittokit.com" class="legal-link">hello@kittokit.com</a></dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <p>kittokit is a non-commercial hobby project with no profit-making intention. For data protection enquiries please use email.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Hosting -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Hosting and Infrastructure</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Cloudflare Pages</h3>
        <p>This website is hosted on <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>. When you visit a page, Cloudflare processes technically necessary connection data as a data processor on our behalf.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Data processed</dt>
            <dd>IP address (potentially anonymised), requested URL, HTTP method, referrer, browser type, timestamp</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Purpose</dt>
            <dd>Website delivery, security, abuse prevention</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interest in operating a publicly accessible website</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>Server logs for up to 7 days, then deleted automatically</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Recipient / third country</dt>
            <dd>Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA — transfers to the USA are covered by EU Standard Contractual Clauses (Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR) and the Cloudflare Data Processing Addendum</dd>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Analytics -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Analytics</h2>

        <h3>3.1 Cloudflare Web Analytics</h3>
        <p>We use Cloudflare Web Analytics — a privacy-friendly measurement system that sets no cookies and performs no cross-site tracking. No personal profiles are created.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Data processed</dt>
            <dd>Pseudonymised page views, referrer, approximate geolocation (country), browser type, screen size — no individual user profile</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interest in aggregated usage analysis to improve the website without profiling</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>Aggregated data for up to 90 days</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Recipient / third country</dt>
            <dd>Cloudflare, Inc., USA — EU Standard Contractual Clauses (see 2.1)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Opt-out</dt>
            <dd>Because no personal profiles are created and no cookie is set, a formal opt-out is not required. The measurement respects the Do-Not-Track header sent by your browser.</dd>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>3.2 Microsoft Clarity (planned)</h3>
        <p>We plan to use <strong>Microsoft Clarity</strong> to analyse user interactions (heatmaps and session recordings). This service will be <strong>activated only after your explicit consent</strong> via our cookie consent banner.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Data processed</dt>
            <dd>Mouse clicks, scroll behaviour, page navigation, session recordings</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR — consent</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>13 months</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Recipient / third country</dt>
            <dd>Microsoft Corporation, One Microsoft Way, Redmond, WA 98052, USA — EU Standard Contractual Clauses</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Microsoft privacy statement</dt>
            <dd><a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement" class="legal-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">privacy.microsoft.com</a></dd>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Advertising -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Advertising</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Google AdSense (planned, Phase 2)</h3>
        <p>In a later phase we plan to integrate <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to display advertisements. AdSense will likewise be <strong>activated only after your explicit consent</strong>.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Data processed</dt>
            <dd>Browsing behaviour, interest categories, cookie IDs, IP address</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR — consent</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>Up to 13 months</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Recipient / third country</dt>
            <dd>Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA — EU Standard Contractual Clauses</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Google privacy policy</dt>
            <dd><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en" class="legal-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">policies.google.com/privacy</a></dd>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Local storage -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Browser-side Storage (localStorage)</h2>
        <p>To display the website correctly we store two settings exclusively in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>. This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to any server.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Stored items</dt>
            <dd><code>kittokit-theme</code> (light/dark preference), <code>kittokit-lang</code> (language preference)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — technically necessary for correct display; no personal profile is created</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>Until you clear it manually (browser settings → clear site data)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Recipient</dt>
            <dd>None — client-side storage only</dd>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. Tools -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Using the Online Tools</h2>
        <p>All tools on kittokit — converters, calculators, formatters and similar utilities — process your input <strong>exclusively in your browser</strong>. Files, text, and any other input are never transmitted to our servers or any third-party server.</p>
        <p>No data processing by us takes place in this context. The processing is performed solely by your browser on your device.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Contact -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Contact</h2>
        <p>When you contact us by email, we process the data you provide in order to handle your enquiry.</p>
        <div class="legal-dl">
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Data processed</dt>
            <dd>Name (if provided), email address, message content</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Legal basis</dt>
            <dd>Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interest in responding to user enquiries</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Retention</dt>
            <dd>Until the correspondence is concluded, then kept for 3 months and deleted</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-dl__row">
            <dt>Email routing</dt>
            <dd>Email delivery is forwarded via Cloudflare Email Routing (Cloudflare, Inc., USA — see section 2.1)</dd>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. Cookie table -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Cookie and Storage Overview</h2>
        <div class="legal-table-wrap">
          <table class="legal-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Name / key</th>
                <th>Provider</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Type</th>
                <th>Retention</th>
                <th>Legal basis</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>kittokit-theme</code></td>
                <td>Own operation</td>
                <td>Theme preference (light/dark)</td>
                <td>localStorage</td>
                <td>Until manually cleared</td>
                <td>Art. 6(1)(f)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>kittokit-lang</code></td>
                <td>Own operation</td>
                <td>Language preference</td>
                <td>localStorage</td>
                <td>Until manually cleared</td>
                <td>Art. 6(1)(f)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>CF session cookie</td>
                <td>Cloudflare</td>
                <td>Language routing (Accept-Language)</td>
                <td>Session cookie</td>
                <td>Until session ends</td>
                <td>Art. 6(1)(f)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Clarity cookies</td>
                <td>Microsoft</td>
                <td>Heatmaps, session replay (planned)</td>
                <td>Cookie</td>
                <td>13 months</td>
                <td>Art. 6(1)(a) — consent</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>AdSense cookies</td>
                <td>Google</td>
                <td>Personalised advertising (planned)</td>
                <td>Cookie</td>
                <td>Up to 13 months</td>
                <td>Art. 6(1)(a) — consent</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="legal-note">Cookies and localStorage items requiring consent are set only after you have accepted via the consent banner. You may withdraw your consent at any time.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Recipients and third-country transfers -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Recipients and Third-Country Transfers</h2>
        <p>We share personal data only where this is necessary to operate the website or where you have given your consent.</p>
        <p>Cloudflare, Inc. and — following consent — Microsoft Corporation and Google LLC are based in the United States. Transfers to the USA are covered by <strong>EU Standard Contractual Clauses</strong> (Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR) and, where applicable, the EU–U.S. Data Privacy Framework. For details, please refer to the respective providers' privacy policies.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. Your rights -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Your Rights as a Data Subject</h2>
        <p>Under the GDPR you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
        <div class="legal-rights">
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Access (Art. 15 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may request information about the personal data we hold about you.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may request correction of inaccurate or completion of incomplete data.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may request deletion of your data, provided no legal retention obligation applies.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Restriction (Art. 18 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may request that we restrict the processing of your data.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may request that we provide your data in a structured, common, machine-readable format.</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Objection (Art. 21 GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may object at any time to processing based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest).</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="legal-rights__item">
            <dt>Withdrawal of consent (Art. 7(3) GDPR)</dt>
            <dd>You may withdraw any consent you have given at any time with future effect — via the consent banner or by emailing us.</dd>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>To exercise your rights, please contact us by email at the address listed in the <a href="/en/imprint" class="legal-link">Imprint</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- 11. Right to lodge a complaint -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
        <p>You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority if you believe that the processing of your personal data violates the GDPR (Art. 77 GDPR).</p>
        <p>The competent supervisory authority is the data protection authority of the German federal state where the controller is domiciled:</p>
        <address class="legal-address">
          State Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information North Rhine-Westphalia (LDI NRW)<br>
          Kavalleriestraße 2–4, 40213 Düsseldorf, Germany<br>
          <a href="https://www.ldi.nrw.de" class="legal-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">www.ldi.nrw.de</a>
        </address>
        <p>A list of all German data protection authorities is available at: <a href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de/EN/Service/Anschriften/anschriften_table.html" class="legal-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">bfdi.bund.de</a></p>
      </section>

      <!-- 12. Changes -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>12. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to update this privacy policy when the legal situation or our data processing practices change. The current version is always available on this page. We will display a notice on the website for material changes.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 54rem;
    padding-top: var(--space-12);
  }
  .legal-header {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }
  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-h1);
    font-weight: var(--font-fw-h1);
    line-height: var(--font-lh-h1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tighter);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal-meta {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }
  .legal-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-h3);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: var(--font-lh-h3);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .legal h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  .legal p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
    line-height: var(--font-lh-body);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal code {
    font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    background: var(--color-surface-sunk);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: var(--r-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .legal-link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: var(--underline-offset);
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
  }
  .legal-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent-hover); }
  .legal-link:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: var(--r-sm);
  }
  .legal-note {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-infobox {
    background: var(--color-surface-sunk);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .infobox-lead {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .infobox-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .infobox-list li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
    line-height: var(--font-lh-small);
  }
  .infobox-list li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal-dl {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .legal-dl__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .legal-dl__row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .legal-dl__row dt {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding-top: 0.1em;
  }
  .legal-dl__row dd {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--font-lh-small);
  }
  .legal-address {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    background: var(--color-surface-sunk);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    display: block;
  }
  .legal-rights {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal-rights__item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 14rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }
  .legal-rights__item dt {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .legal-rights__item dd {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--font-lh-small);
  }
  .legal-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
  }
  .legal-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    min-width: 36rem;
  }
  .legal-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    background: var(--color-surface-sunk);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .legal-table td {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    vertical-align: top;
    line-height: var(--font-lh-small);
  }
  .legal-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .legal h1 { font-size: var(--font-size-h2); }
    .legal-dl__row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-1); }
    .legal-rights__item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-1); }
    .legal-rights__item dd { padding-left: var(--space-3); }
  }
</style>
